Customize the Embedded Pre-Chat Form

Gather contact information and learn about customer needs before chatting. Create a custom pre-chat form and associate Salesforce records like leads, cases, and contacts.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Embedded Service setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Embedded Chat:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026...

When you design your pre-chat form, select a use case that automatically associates information from the form to Salesforce records.

Use Cases to Associate Pre-Chat Information with Salesforce Records
IF YOU SELECT:	THEN SALESFORCE ASSOCIATES THE PRE-CHAT INFORMATION WITH THESE RECORD TYPES:
Sales	Lead records
Service	

Contact records

Case records


Basic	Contact records

You can select the fields that are shown on the pre-chat form, change the order of the fields, and make fields required.

To set up the pre-chat form:

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Embedded Service...
Select the record type that’s created from the pre-chat form.
Click Next.
Select the fields shown on the pre-chat form.
To add a field, click +. You can add only fields that are available on the object.

To create custom labels for your form:

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Rename Tabs and Labels...
Set your primary deployment language from the Select Language dropdown list.
Enter the singular and plural forms of the new tab name...
title: Customizing Embedded Service Pre-chat Forms
